Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.70,1:18:33.33,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎更多大选黑入、更多平民政治\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}more election hacking, more populism,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.91,1:18:36.96,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎让人更加分散注意力 ‎无法集中在真正的问题上…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}more distraction and inability to focus on the real issues...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.96,1:18:39.21,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎那只是社会\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}that's just society.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.34,1:18:46.38,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎现在社会无法自愈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}And now society is incapable of healing itself
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.47,1:18:48.51,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎转移成了一种混乱的形式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}and just devolving into a kind of chaos.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.97,1:18:54.93,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这影响着每一个人 ‎即使你不使用这些产品\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}This affects everyone, even if you don't use these products.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.02,1:18:57.52,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这些事情变成了数码的科学怪人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}These things have become digital Frankensteins
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.60,1:19:00.06,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎让这个世界变成他们现象中的样子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}that are terraforming the world in their image,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.15,1:19:01.86,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎不论是儿童的心理健康\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}whether it's the mental health of children
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.94,1:19:04.48,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎还是我们的政治 我们的政治演说\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}or our politics and our political discourse,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.57,1:19:07.49,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎而不用因为控制公众舆论 ‎承担责任\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}without taking responsibility for taking over the public square.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.57,1:19:10.57,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎-所以 还是要回到… ‎-你觉得这一切怪谁？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}-So, again, it comes back to-And who do you think's responsible?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.66,1:19:13.58,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我认为我们必须让平台负起责任\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}I think we have to have the platforms be responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.66,1:19:15.58,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎因为他们接管大选广告的时候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}for when they take over election advertising,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.66,1:19:17.79,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎就要负责保护大选\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}they're responsible for protecting elections.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.87,1:19:20.38,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎当他们接管儿童心理健康 ‎或是儿童频道的时候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}When they take over mental health of kids or Saturday morning,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.46,1:19:22.71,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎他们就有责任保护好儿童频道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}they're responsible for protecting Saturday morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.71,1:19:27.92,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎保持人们关注的竞争不会结束\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}The race to keep people's attention isn't going away.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.38,1:19:31.85,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们的技术会在我们生活中更加集成 ‎而不会减少\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Our technology's gonna become more integrated into our lives, not less.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.93,1:19:34.89,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎人工智能会更加擅长预判 ‎什么内容能让我们持续盯着屏幕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}The AIs are gonna get better at predicting what keeps us on the screen,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.97,1:19:37.10,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎而不是做出更差的预判\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}not worse at predicting what keeps us on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.94,1:19:42.02,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我已经62岁了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}I... I am 62 years old,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.11,1:19:45.15,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎随着这个对话继续进行 ‎我每一分钟都在变老\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}getting older every minute, the more this conversation goes on...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.23,1:19:47.36,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎但我会告诉你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}...but... but I will tell you that,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.70,1:19:52.37,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎到时候我可能已经死了 不在了 ‎但我可能会为此感恩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}I'm probably gonna be dead and gone, and I'll probably be thankful for it,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.45,1:19:54.33,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎因为当这些恐怖的东西结出恶果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}when all this shit comes to fruition.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.79,1:19:59.58,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我觉得能吓死我\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Because... Because I think that this scares me to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.92,1:20:03.04,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎你也这样看吗？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Do... Do you... Do you see it the same way?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.54,1:20:06.88,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎还是我对一个我不够了解的情况 ‎过度反应了？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Or am I overreacting to a situation that I don't know enough about?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.93,1:20:11.59,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎你最担心什么？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}What are you most worried about?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.85,1:20:18.48,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我认为在最短的时间范围内…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}I think, in the... in the shortest time horizon...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.52,1:20:20.52,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎是内战\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}civil war.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.44,1:20:29.90,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎如果现在的常态继续下去 ‎我们说再过20年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}If we go down the current status quo for, let's say, another 20 years...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.11,1:20:34.57,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们很可能会因为故意无知 ‎毁掉我们的文明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}we probably destroy our civilization through willful ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.66,1:20:37.95,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们或许会无法应对气候变化的挑战\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}We probably fail to meet the challenge of climate change.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.04,1:20:42.08,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们或许会瓦解世界的民主\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}We probably degrade the world's democracies
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.17,1:20:46.13,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎最终衰落成一种奇怪的独裁机能障碍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}so that they fall into some sort of bizarre autocratic dysfunction.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.21,1:20:48.42,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们或许会毁掉全球经济\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}We probably ruin the global economy.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.17,1:20:52.26,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们或许会无法存活\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC} we probably, um, don't survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.34,1:20:54.80,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我真的把它看做 ‎人类生死存亡的大问题\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}You know, I... I really do view it as existential.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.52,1:21:04.98,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这会是知道在这种幻象发生之前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Is this the last generation of people
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.06,1:21:08.48,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎世界是什么样的最后一代人吗？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}that are gonna know what it was like before this illusion took place?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.07,1:21:14.57,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎如果你不知道自己在矩阵中 ‎你要怎么从矩阵中醒来？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Like, how do you wake up from the matrix when you don't know you're in the matrix?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.74,1:21:23.25,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,{\an8}‎（“不论是乌托邦还是毁灭 ‎都是一场一触即发的接力赛…）\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.33,1:21:27.29,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,{\an8}‎（直接通往最后一刻…” ‎巴克敏斯特·富勒）\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.38,1:21:30.63,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎你知道 我们说的很多话 ‎听起来像是…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}A lot of what we're saying sounds like it's just this...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.51,1:21:33.68,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎片面的悲观\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}one-sided doom and gloom.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.76,1:21:36.80,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎“天啊 技术正在毁灭世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Like, " my God, technology's just ruining the world
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.89,1:21:38.05,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎正在毁灭孩子们”\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}and it's ruining kids,"
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.14,1:21:39.26,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎不是这样的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}and it's like... "No."
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.22,1:21:45.56,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这很困惑 ‎因为这同时是乌托邦和毁灭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}It's confusing because it's simultaneous utopia...and dystopia.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.94,1:21:50.44,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我可以在手机按一个按钮 ‎30秒后就能出现一辆车\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC} Like, I could hit a button on my phone, and a car shows up in 30 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.53,1:21:52.69,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我就可以去想去的任何地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}and I can go exactly where I need to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.78,1:21:55.66,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这简直是魔法 太神奇了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}That is magic. That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.16,1:21:57.66,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们制作“点赞”按钮的时候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}When we were making the like button,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.74,1:22:01.49,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们全部的动机是 “我们可以 ‎在世界中传播积极和爱吗？”\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}our entire motivation was, "Can we spread positivity and love in the world?"
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.58,1:22:05.00,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎时间快进到当下 ‎青少年会因为没有得到足够多的点赞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}The idea that, fast-forward to today, and teens would be getting depressed
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.08,1:22:06.37,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎而抑郁 这个想法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}when they don't have enough likes,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.46,1:22:08.63,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎或者会导致政治两极分化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}or it could be leading to political polarization
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.71,1:22:09.88,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎当时是完全无法想象的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}was nowhere on our radar.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.96,1:22:12.13,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我不认为这些人 ‎最开始的目标是邪恶的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}I don't think these guys set out to be evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.51,1:22:15.76,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎只是这个商业模式有问题\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}It's just the business model that has a problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.84,1:22:20.22,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎你可以关掉服务 毁掉不管这是什么\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}You could shut down the service and destroy whatever it is
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.31,1:22:24.52,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎200亿美元的股东利益 被起诉…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}$20 billion of shareholder valueand get sued and...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.60,1:22:27.10,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎但现实是 覆水难收\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}But you can't, in practice, put the genie back in the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.19,1:22:30.40,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎你可以做出一些小的调整 但是最终\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}You can make some tweaks, but at the end of the day,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.48,1:22:34.03,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎你要增加收益和使用 ‎每一个季度都要增加\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}you've gotta grow revenue and usage, quarter over quarter. It's...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.65,1:22:37.53,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎规模做得越大 越难让任何人改变\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}The bigger it gets, the harder it is for anyone to change.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.49,1:22:43.45,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我看到的是一群被困住的人 ‎被商业模式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}What I see is a bunch of people who are trapped by a business model,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.54,1:22:46.16,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎经济奖励和股东压力困住\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}an economic incentive, and shareholder pressure
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.25,1:22:48.92,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎几乎无法做其他的任何事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}that makes it almost impossible to do something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.00,1:22:50.92,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我认为我们应该接受\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}I think we need to accept that it's okay
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.00,1:22:53.17,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎公司专注于挣钱 是合情合理的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}for companies to be focused on making money.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.25,1:22:55.56,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎不合情合理的是 ‎当没有监管、没有规定、\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}What's not okay is when there's no regulation, no rules,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.56,1:22:56.97,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,没有竞争\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}and no competition,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.97,1:23:00.85,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎公司在充当实际政府部门\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}and the companies are acting as sort of de facto governments.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.93,1:23:03.35,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎然后他们说“我们可以监管自己”\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}And then they're saying, "Well, we can regulate ourselves."
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.43,1:23:05.98,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这肯定是骗人的 怎么可能呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}I mean, that's just a lie. That's just ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.06,1:23:09.15,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎经济奖励可以说运营着世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Financial incentives kind of run the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.23,1:23:12.61,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎所以这个问题的任何解决方案 \N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}so any solution to this problem
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.61,1:23:15.57,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎一定要符合经济奖励\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}has to realign the financial incentives.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.07,1:23:18.78,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这些公司没有需要改变的财政理由\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}There's no fiscal reason for these companies to change.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.86,1:23:21.32,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎所以我才认为 我们需要监管\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}And that is why I think we need regulation.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.41,1:23:24.29,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎手机公司有无数的关于你的敏感数据\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}The phone company has tons of sensitive data about you,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.37,1:23:27.54,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们有很多法律去保证 ‎他们不会利用这些数据做错事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}and we have a lot of laws that make sure they don't do the wrong things.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.62,1:23:31.50,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎在数码隐私上 我们几乎没有立法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}We have almost no laws around digital privacy, for example.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.58,1:23:34.42,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们可以对数据收集和处理收税\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}We could tax data collection and processing
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.50,1:23:37.55,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎原理等同于你交水费\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}the same way that you, for example, pay your water bill
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.63,1:23:39.72,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎监控你自己的用水量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}by monitoring the amount of water that you use.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.80,1:23:43.22,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎让这些公司因为持有的数据资产交税\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}You tax these companies on the data assets that they have.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.30,1:23:44.76,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎就能给他们一个财政理由\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}It gives them a fiscal reason
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.85,1:23:47.85,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎不去获取地球上每一条数据\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}to not acquire every piece of data on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.93,1:23:50.56,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎立法在这方面太落后了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}The law runs way behind on these things,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.65,1:23:55.86,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎但据我所知 当前状况的存在 ‎不是为了保护用户\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}but what I know is the current situation exists not for the protection of users,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.94,1:23:58.70,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎而是为了保护这些巨型的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}but for the protection of the rights and privileges
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.78,1:24:01.45,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎超级富有公司的权利和特权\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}of these gigantic, incredibly wealthy companies.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.24,1:24:05.83,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们要一直听从最有钱 ‎最有权力的人吗？\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Are we always gonna defer to the richest, most powerful people?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.91,1:24:07.41,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎还是我们要说\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Or are we ever gonna say,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.95,1:24:12.04,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎“有时候 确实是有国家利益\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}"You know, there are times when there is a national interest.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.13,1:24:15.59,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎有时候 人民的利益 用户利益\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}There are times when the interests of people, of users,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.67,1:24:17.38,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎其实比一个\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}is actually more important
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.01,1:24:21.47,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎已经是亿万富翁的人的利益 ‎更加重要？”\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}than the profits of somebody who's already a billionaire"?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.89,1:24:26.60,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这些市场削弱了民主 削弱了自由\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}These markets undermine democracy, and they undermine freedom,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.68,1:24:28.52,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎应该对他们进行法律的制裁\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}and they should be outlawed.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.14,1:24:31.81,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这不是激进的提议\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}This is not a radical proposal.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.90,1:24:34.19,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们有法律制裁的其他市场\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}There are other markets that we outlaw.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.27,1:24:36.98,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们制裁人类器官贩卖市场\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}We outlaw markets in human organs.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.07,1:24:39.49,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们制裁人类奴隶市场\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}We outlaw markets in human slaves.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.94,1:24:44.03,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎因为它们都有不可避免的破坏性后果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Because they have inevitable destructive consequences.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.53,1:24:45.83,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们生活的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}We live in a world
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.91,1:24:50.00,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎死去的树比活着的树更有经济价值\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}in which a tree is worth more, financially, dead than alive,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.08,1:24:53.83,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这个世界 死去的鲸 ‎比活着的鲸更有价值\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}in a world in which a whale is worth more dead than alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.92,1:24:56.34,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎只要我们的经济这样运转\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}For so long as our economy works in that way
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.42,1:24:58.13,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎公司不受监管\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}and corporations go unregulated,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.21,1:25:00.67,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎它们就会继续破坏树木\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}they're going to continue to destroy trees,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.76,1:25:01.76,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎继续捕杀鲸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}to kill whales,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.84,1:25:06.10,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎在地球上挖矿 从地下抽石油\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}to mine the earth, and to continue to pull oil out of the ground,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.18,1:25:08.39,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎虽然我们知道 这样做会破坏地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}even though we know it is destroying the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.47,1:25:12.14,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们知道 这样做会为未来几代人 ‎留下一个更不堪的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}and we know that it's going to leave a worse world for future generations.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.23,1:25:13.85,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这是目光短浅\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}This is short-term thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.94,1:25:16.69,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎为了利益牺牲一切的信仰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}based on this religion of profit at all costs,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.77,1:25:20.15,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎指望每个 ‎只顾自己私利的公司会突然神奇地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}as if somehow, magically, each corporation acting in its selfish interest
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.24,1:25:21.95,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎去产生最好的结果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}is going to produce the best result.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.03,1:25:24.49,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这已经影响环境很久了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}This has been affecting the environment for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.57,1:25:27.28,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎恐怖的是 希望这是 ‎压倒骆驼的最后一根稻草\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}What's frightening, and what hopefully is the last straw
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.37,1:25:29.20,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎让我们作为文明的种族 去幡然醒悟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}that will make us wake up as a civilization
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.29,1:25:31.70,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这个理论最初就有很多缺点\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}to how flawed this theory has been in the first place
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.79,1:25:35.00,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎让我们看到 我们现在就是树 就是鲸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}is to see that now we're the tree, we're the whale.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.08,1:25:37.04,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们的关注就是被挖掘的矿产\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Our attention can be mined.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.13,1:25:39.13,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎如果我们花时间盯着一个屏幕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}We are more profitable to a corporation
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.21,1:25:41.59,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎盯着一个广告 对公司而言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}if we're spending time staring at a screen,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.67,1:25:42.97,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎比我们用这个时间\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}staring at an ad,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.05,1:25:45.89,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎过自己丰富的生活 更加有利可图\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}than if we're spending that time living our life in a rich way.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.97,1:25:47.55,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们看到了这样的后果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}And so, we're seeing the results of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.64,1:25:50.68,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们看到公司利用强大的人工智能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}We're seeing corporations using powerful artificial intelligence
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.77,1:25:53.52,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎凌驾在我们的智能之上 ‎研究怎样拉拢我们的关注\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}to outsmart us and figure out how to pull our attention
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.60,1:25:55.35,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎让我们去看 他们想让我们看的东西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}toward the things they want us to look at,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.44,1:25:57.27,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎而不是让我们看 ‎与我们目标、价值观\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}rather than the things that are most consistent
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.36,1:25:59.23,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎与我们的生活最为一致的东西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}with our goals and our values and our lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.99,1:26:04.45,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,{\an8}‎（史蒂夫·乔布斯 今日演讲者）\N\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.53,1:26:06.91,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎电脑对我来说 是…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}What a computer is,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.99,1:26:10.29,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎是我们人类历史上 最神奇的发明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}is it's the most remarkable tool that we've ever come up with.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.12,1:26:13.87,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎相当于是我们思想的自行车\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}And it's the equivalent of a bicycle for our minds.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.62,1:26:20.09,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎人道技术的创想 是硅谷最初的目标\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}The idea of humane technology, that's where Silicon Valley got its start.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.05,1:26:25.72,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们已经背离了这个目标 ‎因为这样做比较酷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}And we've lost sight of it because it became the cool thing to do,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.80,1:26:27.26,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎而不是这样做比较正确\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}as opposed to the right thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.34,1:26:29.72,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎网络就是一个奇怪的、可笑的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}The Internet was, like, a weird, wacky place.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.80,1:26:31.39,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎它是实验性的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}It was experimental.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.47,1:26:34.73,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎网络上发生着有创意的事情 ‎当然现在也有发生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Creative things happened on the Internet, and certainly, they do still,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.81,1:26:38.61,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎但是感觉像一个巨大的商场\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}but, like, it just feels like this, like, giant mall.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.69,1:26:41.54,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎就是“天啊 \N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}You know, it's just like, "God, there's gotta be...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.54,1:26:44.15,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎肯定不止表面上这么简单”\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}there's gotta be more to it than that."
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.74,1:26:48.41,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我想我只是一个乐观主义者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}I guess I'm just an optimist.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.49,1:26:52.04,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎因为我认为 ‎我们可以改变社交媒体的样子和方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}'Cause I think we can change what social media looks like and means.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.08,1:26:56.76,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎技术的工作方式不是物理学定律 \N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}The way the technology works is not a law of physics.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.76,1:26:58.00,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎它不是一成不变的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}It is not set in stone.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.00,1:27:02.17,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这些都是像我这样的人类 ‎做出的选择\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}These are choices that human beings like myself have been making.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.75,1:27:05.34,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎人类可以改变这些技术\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}And human beings can change those technologies.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.97,1:27:09.97,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎现在的问题是 我们是否愿意承认\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}And the question now is whether or not we're willing to admit
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.47,1:27:15.43,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这些后果 是我们杰作的直接产物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}that those bad outcomes are coming directly as a product of our work.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.02,1:27:24.86,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这些东西是我们建立起来的 ‎我们有责任去改变它们\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}It's that we built these things, and we have a responsibility to change it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.21,1:27:38.79,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎提取关注模型 \N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}The attention extraction model
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.79,1:27:42.29,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎不是我们想对待人类的方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}is not how we want to treat human beings.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.09,1:27:48.13,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎只有我这样想吗？还是…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Is it just me or...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.84,1:27:50.84,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎可悲的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Poor sucker.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.51,1:27:53.22,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎一个健康社会的结构\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}The fabric of a healthy society
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.30,1:27:56.14,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎要依靠我们脱离这种 ‎有破坏性的商业模型\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}depends on us getting off this corrosive business model.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.69,1:28:07.78,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们可以要求 ‎这些产品进行人道设计\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}We can demand that these products be designed humanely.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.40,1:28:13.12,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们可以要求 ‎不被当做可以提取的资源对待\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}We can demand to not be treated as an extractable resource.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.16,1:28:18.33,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们的动机可以是 ‎“我们怎样让这个世界变得更好？”\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}The intention could be: "How do we make the world better?"
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.46,1:28:21.58,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎在整个人类历史中 \N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}Throughout history,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.58,1:28:23.79,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎每一次有事物变得更好\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs13\1c&H003CA8DC}every single time something's gotten better,
